    <div class="ing-box"><h4>Green Tea EGCG: What the Science Says</h4><p>EGCG is the most studied polyphenol antioxidant, with over 17,000 published research papers supporting its health benefits.</p><div class="vs-strip">
      <div class="vs-item"><strong>Fat Oxidation</strong><p>Green tea catechins increased fat oxidation by 16% and energy expenditure by ~80 cal/day in a meta-analysis of 11 studies.<br /><em>Int J Obesity, 2009</em></p></div>
      <div class="vs-item"><strong>Weight Management</strong><p>Green tea produced 1.3kg weight loss vs. placebo over 12 weeks across 14 RCTs.<br /><em>Cochrane Review, 2012</em></p></div>
      <div class="vs-item"><strong>Cardiovascular Mortality</strong><p>5+ cups/day of green tea was associated with 26% lower cardiovascular mortality in a 40,530-person, 11-year cohort study.<br /><em>JAMA, 2006</em></p></div>
      <div class="vs-item"><strong>Liver Safety</strong><p>EFSA confirmed that EGCG fewer than 800mg/day from supplements shows no evidence of liver harm in healthy adults.<br /><em>EFSA, 2018</em></p></div>
    </div></div>

